               <head>Grant; Mendlesham, etc.; 1205-1235</head>
               <msContents>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_105422">Mendlesham (Mendlesham etc)</placeName>. 
                        <origDate notBefore="1205" notAfter="1235">1205-1235</origDate>. 
                        Grant from <persName>
                           <forename>Geoffrey</forename> 
                           <surname>Dorliens</surname>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Dorliens">
                           <forename>Agatha</forename> his wife</persName>, to <persName nymRef="Prech">
                           <forename>John</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Roger</forename> 
                              <surname>Prech</surname>
                           </persName></persName>, of two acres of land, called <placeName type="minor">Orlienescroft</placeName>, held of the house of <placeName type="manor" key="place_113015">Snape</placeName> at a yearly rent 16d. The said John is to pay a yearly rent of 16d. and half a pound of pepper, at the feast of the Assumption of the Virgin, and to be responsible to the prior and monks of Snape for the rent due to them; and has done homage and paid a fine of 19s. of silver [1205-35]
                        Witnesses. <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> le <surname>Flameng</surname></persName>, <persName nymRef="Flameng">
                           <forename>Richard</forename>
                        </persName> and <persName nymRef="Flameng">
                           <forename>John</forename></persName>, his sons, <persName>
                           <forename>Hubert</forename> 
                           <surname>Cordebof</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Ranulf</forename> of <surname>Becclinger</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> le <surname>Man</surname></persName>, <persName>John Squier</persName>; Radulf, Walter, Roger, servants of Snape, and many others.
                     The seal is wanting. 
                     </p>
